markets.title: Will more than 95.5 million Americans have **COVID-19 boosters** by March 9?
markets.subtitle: >95,500K
markets.rules_primary: If over 95.5 million fully vaccinated Americans are reported as having received a booster shot for COVID-19 by March 9, 2022, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: This market will close and expire the sooner of the first 10:00 AM ET following the occurrence of the event, the first 10:00 AM ET following the release of data for March 9, 2022 or March 17, 2022.

markets.title: Will more than 62 million Americans receive a **booster shot** for COVID-19 by December 20, 2021?
markets.subtitle: >62m
markets.rules_primary: If over 62 million fully vaccinated Americans are reported as having received a booster shot for COVID-19 by December 20, 2021, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: Please note that the value used to determine the contract is the value as recorded on the CDC website at 11:00 AM on December 20, 2021 . Revisions to that value to incorporate more recent data that is published after that time is not used to determine the contract.
